  "prompt": "If I buy wireless Bluetooth headphones with a USB charger, will they work like wired headphones if they're plugged into my computer usb via USB cable?",
  "response": "Typically, wireless Bluetooth headphones will not work as wired headphones when plugged into a USB port. Most Bluetooth headphones use USB cables only for charging the battery, not for audio transmission. \n\nTo use them as wired headphones, you would need a pair that specifically supports USB audio input. Some higher-end models do offer this feature, but it's not common in most Bluetooth wireless headphones.\n\nIf you want headphones that can work both wirelessly and wired, look for models that:\n1. Have a detachable audio cable\n2. Specifically mention USB audio support\n3. Come with a 3.5mm audio cable or USB audio cable\n\nOtherwise, you'll need to use them in Bluetooth mode or switch to a different set of wired headphones for direct USB audio connection.",
